OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1782386302
OL,3,CKeir Starmer condemns attack on Gurkha
OL,4,Cveterans who were told 'go home'
OL,6,FThe Nepalese soldiers have been part
OL,7,Fof the British Army for more than 200
OL,8,Fyears and were granted the right to
OL,9,Fsettle in the UK in 2009.
OL,11,FAt Prime Minister's Questions, the
OL,12,FLabour MP for Aldershot said: "In a
OL,13,Fweek when we salute those who have
OL,14,Fserved and are serving our country,
OL,15,Felderly Gurkha veterans were assaulted
OL,16,Fin the park, by our war memorial, and
OL,17,Ftold to go home.
OL,26,@tD@_OU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1782386302
OL,3,CKeir Starmer condemns attack on Gurkha
OL,4,Cveterans who were told 'go home'
OL,6,F"Will the Prime Minister and the House
OL,7,Fjoin me in standing against this
OL,8,Fdespicable attack and commend the
OL,9,Fheroism of our Gurkhas?
OL,11,F"And does he agree with me that now is
OL,12,Fthe time to resolve the longstanding
OL,13,Fissues on Gurkha pensions we have been
OL,14,Fworking towards, because the Gurkhas
OL,15,Fhave given so much for our country?"
OL,17,FSir Keir replied: "The racist attack
OL,18,Fshe describes is utterly disgraceful,
OL,19,Fand I condemn it, and I hope the whole
OL,20,FHouse will condemn it.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUwD@dO]yD@SOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
